direction: right

TelegramBot: {
  shape: cylinder
  label: "Telegram Bot (User Interface)"
}
BinanceAPI: {
  shape: cloud
  label: "Binance API (Data Source)"
}
Redis: {
  shape: cylinder
  label: "Redis Cache (Live Data/Locks)"
}
PostgreSQL: {
  shape: cylinder
  label: "PostgreSQL DB (Persistent Data)"
}

TelegramBot -> main.py: User Commands/Messages
main.py -> bot/handlers.py: Handle Telegram Updates
bot/handlers.py -> PostgreSQL: Store/Retrieve User Config/Tracked Coins

main.py -> TradeMonitor: Initialize Background Tasks
TradeMonitor -> BinanceAPI: WebSocket Streams (miniTicker, kline)
TradeMonitor -> Redis: Cache Live Prices/Klines
TradeMonitor -> AIEngine: Trigger Analysis on Candle Close/Scan
TradeMonitor -> PostgreSQL: Monitor Live Trades, Update Status

AIEngine -> Redis: Get Cached OHLCV, Acquire Locks
AIEngine -> BinanceAPI: Fetch Historical OHLCV (REST)
AIEngine -> strategies.py: Calculate Scores, Get Trade Params
AIEngine -> PostgreSQL: Store Shadow Trades, Live Trades

strategies.py -> pandas: Data Manipulation

PostgreSQL -> Redis: (Implicit) Data consistency needs
Redis -> PostgreSQL: (Implicit) Data consistency needs
